(
<figureCitation box="[948,1096,1790,1812]" captionStart-0="Figure 128" captionStart-1="Figure 129" captionStart-2="Figure 130" captionStart-3="Figure 131" captionStart-4="Figure 132" captionStart-5="Figure 133" captionStartId-0="209.[162,240,1839,1858]" captionStartId-1="210.[142,220,1839,1858]" captionStartId-2="211.[162,240,1839,1858]" captionStartId-3="212.[142,220,1839,1858]" captionStartId-4="213.[162,240,1839,1858]" captionStartId-5="214.[142,220,1839,1858]" captionTargetBox-0="[258,1344,195,1805]" captionTargetBox-1="[203,1359,196,1804]" captionTargetBox-2="[239,1364,195,1805]" captionTargetBox-3="[191,1373,195,1804]" captionTargetBox-4="[222,1382,196,1805]" captionTargetBox-5="[202,1360,195,1805]" captionTargetId-0="figure-80@209.[258,1345,194,1806]" captionTargetId-1="figure-84@210.[203,1360,194,1806]" captionTargetId-2="figure-81@211.[239,1365,194,1806]" captionTargetId-3="figure-69@212.[190,1374,194,1806]" captionTargetId-4="figure-75@213.[222,1382,194,1806]" captionTargetId-5="figure-84@214.[202,1361,194,1806]" captionTargetPageId-0="209" captionTargetPageId-1="210" captionTargetPageId-2="211" captionTargetPageId-3="212" captionTargetPageId-4="213" captionTargetPageId-5="214" captionText-0="Figure 128. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: paratype ♂, 6.5 × 3.3 mm, cephalothorax 1.82 mm wide, habitus lateral, pleon dorsal; holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, cephalothorax lateral, dorsal, frontal (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-1="Figure 129. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, maxilliped caudal, maxilliped distal part enlarged, frontal; paratype ♀, 3.5 mm wide, cephalothorax 1.80 mm wide, all other mouthparts, first antenna (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-2="Figure 130. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopods 1–3 frontal, uropod dorsal and ventral; paratype ♀, 3.5 mm wide, cephalothorax 1.80 mm wide, second antenna flagellum (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-3="Figure 131. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopods 4–6 frontal, pereiopod 4 dactylus frontal and caudal (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-4="Figure 132. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pereiopod 7 frontal and caudal, second antenna ventral, sesond antenna apical cone enlarged (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." captionText-5="Figure 133. Scleropactes pululahua sp. nov.: holotype ♂, 6.6 × 3.0 mm, cephalothorax 1.57 mm wide, pleopods 1–4 frontal, pleopod 5 caudal; paratype ♀, 3.5 mm wide, cephalothorax 1.80 mm wide, pleopods 1 and 2 frontal (Ecuador, Pichincha Prov., Pululahua volcano, altitude 3000 m, leg. L. Bartolozzi, 14 February 1993, MZUF)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430342" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430344" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430346" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430348" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430350" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5430352" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5430342/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5430344/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5430346/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5430348/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5430350/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/5430352/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Figs 128–133</figureCitation>
